{"questionId":"9066486","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Lithium has many uses.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Lithium forms a crystalline lattice with the unit cell structure shown below.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c0162aef5ac3dda74599b7deb5b89131ef914c26.png\" width=\"215\" height=\"208\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">X-ray diffraction shows that the length of the edge of the unit cell is 3.51 × 10<sup>−8</sup> cm.</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Determine the density of lithium, in g cm<sup>−3</sup>, using sections 2 and 6 of the data booklet.</span></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">mass of Li in unit cell = «&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2 \\times \\frac{{6.94{\\text{ g mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}{{6.02 \\times {{10}^{23}}{\\text{ mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}}}}\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6.94</mn>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;g mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>6.02</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>23</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>&nbsp;mo</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mtext>l</mtext>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n   